Interface ApplicationBuilder<A extends Application<A>,S extends ApplicationSchema<A,S>>

Type Parameters:
A - the type of the Applications the ApplicationBuilder will realize
S - the type of the ApplicationSchema for the Applications

AbstractApplicationBuilder, AbstractJavaApplicationBuilder, ExternalJavaApplicationBuilder, SimpleApplicationBuilder, VirtualizedJavaApplicationBuilder
public interface ApplicationBuilder<A extends Application<A>,S extends ApplicationSchema<A,S>>

An ApplicationBuilder is responsible the creation of Applications based on ApplicationSchemas.

Author:
Brian Oliver

Method Summary
 A realize(S schema)
          Realizes an instance of an Application (without a name and using a NullApplicationConsole).
 A realize(S schema, String applicationName)
          Realizes an instance of an Application (using a SystemApplicationConsole).

Method Detail

realize

A realize(S schema,
          String applicationName,
          ApplicationConsole console)
                                 throws IOException
Realizes an instance of an Application.

Parameters:
schema - the ApplicationSchema to use for realizing the Application
applicationName - the name of the application
console - the ApplicationConsole that will be used for I/O by the realized Application. This may be null if not required
Returns:
an Application representing the application realized by the ApplicationBuilder
Throws:
IOException - when a problem occurs while starting the application
